{"word":"ἔνδοθεν","slug":"ἔνδοθεν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔνδοθεν</b></el>  (e)/ndoqen) adverb<p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔνδον'><el>ἔνδον</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>from within</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>intrinsecus</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἔνδοθεν στέγης</el> <i>from inside</i> the tent, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <el>οἴκοθεν</el>, <i>of oneself, by one's own doing</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>within</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>οἱ ἔνδοθεν</el> <i>the domestics</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; or <i>the people inside the city</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}